    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"NGL-3 expressed in non-neural cells induces functional presynaptic differentiation in contacting axons\"\nFig.3: \"Overexpression of NGL-3 in cultured neurons increases excitatory, but not inhibitory, presynaptic contacts on dendrites of transfected neurons\"\nFig.5: \"Knockdown of NGL-3 leads to decreases in the number and function of excitatory synapses\"\nFig.7: \"Soluble LAR reduces NGL-3-induced presynaptic differentiation\". Experimental description: Dissociated culture is of rat species: \" Briefly, primary hippocampal neuron cultures at 10 d in vitro (10 DIV) prepared from embryonic day 18-19 (E18-19) rats were cocultured with HEK293T cells expressing NGLs, LAR or EGFP, followed by immunostaining at 13 DIV. \"\n\n15/01/2018 Pim\n- Overexpressed LRRC4b is of rat species: \"Full-length human NGL-1 (NM_020929, amino acids 1-641) and rat NGL-3 (XM_218615, amino acids 1-709) were subcloned into pEGFP-N1 (Clontech).\"",
